{"word":"H8672 - תֵּשַׁע - têshaʻ - tay'-shah - Nine","slug":"H8672","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">תֵּשַׁע</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>têshaʻ"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>tay'-shah"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Nine"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05EA;&#x05BC;&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05E2;&#x05D4;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05EA;&#x05BC;&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05E2; - te&#x0302;sha&#x201B;  tish&#x201B;a&#x0302;h</b> - <i>tay'-shah, tish-aw'</i><p/>The second form is the masculine of the first; perhaps from <a href=\"#/H8159\">H8159</a> through the idea of a <i>turn</i> to the next or full number ten; <i>nine</i> or (ordinal) <i>ninth: - </i>nine (+ -teen, + -teenth, -th)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H8449\">H8449</a>, <a href=\"#/H8623\">H8623</a>, <a href=\"#/H8630\">H8630</a>, <a href=\"#/H8633\">H8633</a>, <a href=\"#/H8634\">H8634</a>, <a href=\"#/H8638\">H8638</a>, <a href=\"#/H8640\">H8640</a>, <a href=\"#/H8645\">H8645</a>, <a href=\"#/H8646\">H8646</a>, <a href=\"#/H8650\">H8650</a>, <a href=\"#/H8654\">H8654</a>, <a href=\"#/H8655\">H8655</a>, <a href=\"#/H8657\">H8657</a>, <a href=\"#/H8658\">H8658</a>, <a href=\"#/H8659\">H8659</a>, <a href=\"#/H8660\">H8660</a>, <a href=\"#/H8661\">H8661</a>, <a href=\"#/H8662\">H8662</a>, <a href=\"#/H8671\">H8671</a>, <a href=\"#/H8673\">H8673</a>"}]}